# GodTier Shorts Progress Memory Rule

Use `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` at the repository root as the canonical handoff memory for ongoing work.

## Required Workflow

- Read `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` before planning, editing files, or running broad verification.
- If `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` does not exist, create it using the required sections from this rule before continuing.
- After every meaningful milestone, update `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` so the next AI agent can resume without rebuilding context from scratch.
- Before ending a work session, make sure `PROJECT_MEMORY.md` reflects the latest state, remaining work, blockers, and validation status.

## What Must Be Recorded

- `Current Objective`: the task currently being worked on and why it matters.
- `Current State`: confirmed repo facts, constraints, and any relevant in-progress changes.
- `Decisions In Force`: non-obvious implementation or process decisions future work must preserve.
- `Open Work / Next Steps`: ordered follow-ups, remaining tasks, blockers, and assumptions.
- `Validation Status`: commands run, what passed, what failed, and what was not run.
- `Key References`: exact file paths for the docs, reports, tests, or scripts that justify the current state.
- `Session Log`: brief dated entries for meaningful progress, newest entry first.

## Writing Rules

- Keep entries concise, factual, and easy to scan.
- Prefer exact file paths, commands, and concrete outcomes over vague summaries.
- Record blockers and unverified assumptions explicitly.
- Do not delete unresolved context just to keep the file short; compress older detail instead.
- When the active objective changes, rewrite `Current Objective`, refresh `Open Work / Next Steps`, and add a `Session Log` entry.
- When work completes, note the final status and the most natural next starting point for the next session.

## Scope Notes

- Treat `.agents/rules/*` as canonical AI rules for this repo.
- Treat `.cursor/rules/*` as compatibility mirrors of `.agents/rules/*`, not independent sources of truth.
- This rule complements `.agents/rules/godtier-shorts.mdc`; both should remain in effect.

